# Production-Only Workflow

**CRITICAL**: This project is tested and verified EXCLUSIVELY in production. Never test on local or dev.

## Forbidden Actions

Do NOT do any of the following:

- ❌ Run `npm run dev`, `pnpm dev`, `vite`, `tsx watch`, or any local server
- ❌ Navigate to `localhost`, `127.0.0.1`, or `http://localhost:5173` in the browser tool
- ❌ Curl `localhost` endpoints to debug
- ❌ Suggest the user "open the app locally" or "start dev server"
- ❌ Ask the user to "check the browser console in dev"

## Required Workflow

1. **Code verification (local, no server)**:
   - TypeScript: `npm --prefix client run build` or `tsc --noEmit`
   - Lint: use the ReadLints tool
   - Unit/integration tests only

2. **Deploy to production**:
   - `git push heroku main:master`

3. **Verify in production**:
   - `heroku logs --tail --app <app>`
   - Use browser tool against the PRODUCTION URL only: `https://ail.mysalesforcedemo.com`
   - Do NOT use `*.herokuapp.com` URLs — always use `https://ail.mysalesforcedemo.com`
   - Check real production console errors (the user pastes them)

## When Debugging Runtime Errors

- User shares production console errors (e.g. minified `index-*.js` stack traces)
- Fix the source
- Verify compilation cleanly: `npm --prefix client run build`
- Commit and deploy; verify in production

## When In Doubt

Ask: "Should I deploy to production to test this?" - never "Should I run it locally?"
